@ijuma @rajinisivaram 

> is there a strong reason to allow a different way of specifying the JAAS file?

It is just to enable a uniform way of passing parameters. Removing it and allowing it to be set strictly via a system property also works. Note that the system property has priority over the command-line option in the case both are set.

@gwenshap Ready for re-review. Note that the system test has uncovered a few issues which I fixed in the last couple of commits -- they are unrelated except for the fact that the REST API system test revealed them.

The only comment I don't think I directly addressed was the `PUT` vs `POST`. I can see arguments both ways, so I'm not tied to either in particular. Let me know if you'd prefer the `PUT` version, it should only be a couple of lines change.

I'm also aware of one other issue that can cause system test failures -- because sink tasks join their consumer group during their start(), and that start() currently occurs in the DistributedHerder's worker thread, it can cause that thread to block for long enough to miss heartbeats, then have to rejoin (which can also take awhile as other members need to heartbeat). As far as I can tell, nothing fundamentally breaks and we could probably resolve it just by increasing timeouts in the test (the failure is that some data doesn't appear downstream as quickly as we would like, but it should get there eventually once all the membership issues are worked out). However, I'd also just like to figure out how to get that work out of the DistributedHerder's thread -- invoking any 3rd party code in that thread is potentially risky. I don't think we want to roll that into this patch though.
